The food here was amazing! Without naming any other known “soul food” spots close by, this by far was the best so far! This was the 4th on my list and I’m very impressed! And I’m not usually a reviews kind of guy. They really season the food right, flavorful, WITHOUT over-salting, and all the sides I had, which included stuffing, yams, fries, cornbread, and plantains, were all great compliments to my entrees. For a guy who grew up in Mississippi and Louisiana, and has been looking for a good spot, Miss Mamie’s DEFINITELY gets my stamp of approval!  Thank you!

Finding a African american restaurant on the upper west side of NYC is like looking for a needle in a pin stack. I think this is literally the only one. I was passing through her for a client who swears by their food. He’s a older white guy who if not for him I would have missed out on the best tasting banana pudding I’ve had In memory. It’s my favorite desert and theirs had some southern black magic mixed in it. I wish I had purchased two servings. Theirs some nice history around this establishment and I suggest you go there, look at the old photos lining the walls and enjoy some really delicious food. #southernfoodnyc #africanamericanrestaurantnyc #foodnyc #upperwestsidenyc #nyc #uws #bananapudding #kingofcoffeenyc #kingofmarijuananyc #sankofatafari  UPDATE!!! The yams and collard greens are what's going to bring me back. OMG!!!! They are delicious. So, i ordered the Miss Mamie Sampler and honey it was just enough to make me order a plate. It is worth the money. Try it!!! I then shared a combination entree of ribs and fried chicken.  As you can see in the picture, we ate all the meat. We were full to capacity!!!!! Only downfall was the cornbread and the card machine being down. If it would've been online l, then the tip would've been higher. But, i must say.....this place is definitely worth the try.

His main responsibility seemed to stand by/near/around the bar, chat with the two people already there, talk a little bit of unoriginal politics and then sing along to the playlist.  The young lady who did eventually wait on us was incredibly sweet and efficient but it's just weird with a staff of two to have one person hanging out doing sweet f-a. Tip well and tip cash so Sir Hangabout doesn't try to lay any claims.

Incredibly slow service! My family and I went for an early dinner. It was not particularly crowded, but took forever for the food to come. My husband ordered an appetizer that ended up not coming out! It was a good hour and a half wait before we got our food!! We were told that they were short staffed and the chef was taking orders and cooking the food. There was a lady there that was helping with order taking, but she was also very slow moving. We should’ve been told that there would be an extended wait due to the fact that they were short staffed. I also feel since we waited so long we should’ve been offered a complimentary drink or appetizer or something. As for the food, it was just ok! My husband’s chicken was not cooked all the way through. The ribs were salty. The rice and peas were bland! Went to this place today. The interieur ist not what you might expect but the food, especially the BBQ chicken and the peach cobbler were amazingly good.

I visited Miss Mamie's Spoonbread Too  yesterday afternoon around 12:45 pm. I was accompanied by my 5 year old son and a good friend if mine. The decor was and upkeep of the restaurant was poor at best. It appeared as if it hadn't been mopped in quite a while. My friend and I both had Salmon. I had calaloo greens and candied yams and my friend had the macaroni and cheese and another side I can't seem to recall at this time. My son had the stew chicken and collard greens. All dishes come with rice and peas. At 12:45 in the afternoon, our rice and peas was not fresh at all. Most of it was comprised of burnt, hard, reheated, and maybe reheated again rice grains that obviously was scraped from the bottom of the pot from a day or two before. Everything on our plates were loaded with sugar with the exception of the calaloo. If you are diabetic, you would certainly be on your way to a diabetic coma. If you are not diabetic, after a meal there, you certainly would be. The meal there was highly disappointing and to think they thought it was okay to serve food in that manner. Nothing on those plates were fresh. The salmon was frozen and certainly microwaved. It was rubbery and sweet. If I wanted left-overs I certainly would have better luck with a 1 week old meal from thanksgiving dinner. I would not recommend this place at all. I was highly disappointed.  The doggie bag (we did not ask for) went straight into the garbage bag at Central Park. Btw... the restroom... no bueno!
Not a bad place. The chicken and catfish are great!
Amazing food and service, Althea was amazing! Cornbread and homemade iced tea are my favorites! I'm from STL so I look forward to coming back!

Great food: I recommend the fry chicken with mac and cheese and the handcut handmade french fries. The pork with marinated onions is also really good and the corn bread is complementary and delicious. They also have good desserts.
